<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF94BA38B3E3F3C7BB7AFB06" box="[2033,2396,1191,1224]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF94BA38B3E3F3C7BB7AFB06" blockId="40.[2032,2626,1073,1501]" box="[2033,2396,1191,1224]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">This species is monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF94BA38B3E2F3AFBB6BFAA8" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" type="distribution">
<caption id="C5946657FF94BA38B3E2F3AFBB6BFAA8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6567902" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6567902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6567902/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" targetBox="[1417,2009,1083,1498]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF94BA38B3E2F3AFBB6BFAA8" blockId="40.[2032,2626,1073,1501]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFF94BA38B3E2F3AFBA87FB3E" bold="true" box="[2032,2209,1231,1264]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="532FF83DFF94BA38BD74F3AFBA0BFAD9" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Barat" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">West Java Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFF94BA38BC58F39ABAF1FAD9" box="[2122,2263,1274,1303]" name="Indonesia" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, known only from two localities, Cibadak and Cibodas, in the Bogor area just S ofJakarta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF94BA38B3E2F20DB4C7F9B4" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" type="description">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF94BA38B3E2F20DB4C7F9B4" blockId="40.[2032,2626,1073,1501]" lastBlockId="40.[1417,2626,1507,2369]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFF94BA38B3E2F20DBACDFA40" bold="true" box="[2032,2283,1389,1422]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 79-86 mm, tail 30-43 mm, ear ¢. 
<quantity id="56139B3AFF94BA38BD08F2F8BBA4FA7B" box="[2330,2434,1432,1461]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
, forearm 59-60 mm; weight 26-27 g. Fur is short and velvety, deep blackish brown on head and back, paler on crown, with a distinct grayishbuff mantle with grizzled margins across neck and upper back; underparts are pale brown. Ears are large and finely covered with small horny points. Skin on forearm and ear membraneis furred.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF94BA38B199F1E5B473F840" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF94BA38B199F1E5B473F840" blockId="40.[1417,2626,1507,2369]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFF94BA38B199F1E5B7DCF96C" bold="true" box="[1419,1530,1669,1698]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659">Habitat.</emphasis>
Two males were observed (one collected) in a nesting hole of a barbet or woodpecker, in the dead limb of a rubbertree at Cibadak, at 
<quantity id="56139B3AFF94BA38BCE0F1CCBB6EF907" box="[2290,2376,1708,1737]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
altitude, in 1938, and two males were collected from a tree hollow at Cibodas, at 
<quantity id="56139B3AFF94BA38BD22F1B4BBB0F93F" box="[2352,2454,1748,1777]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" unit="m" value="1450.0">1450 m</quantity>
altitude, in 1990. Cibadak now forms part of the urban area of Bogorcity; at the time of collection it was humid tropical forest and rubber plantations. Cibodas retains a large botanical garden and national park and the remaining habitat is volcanic, submontane, humid tropical forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF94BA38B199F0F5B5A6F878" box="[1419,1920,1941,1974]" pageId="40" pageNumber="659" type="food_feeding">
